description:
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Job Title: &lt;/strong&gt;Dental Nurse Apprentice&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Salary: Age dependant&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;21 to 24 £8.20 per hour&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;18 to 20 £6.45 per hour&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Under 18 £4.55 per hour&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Hours: &lt;/strong&gt;37.5 per week&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Responsible to: &lt;/strong&gt;Clinical Lead Dental Nurse&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Accountable to: &lt;/strong&gt;Clinical Operations Manager&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Location: &lt;/strong&gt;Harleigh Road Dental Centre, Bodmin&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Role summary: &lt;/strong&gt;This is an exciting opportunity to learn and develop as a dental nurse. Following initial training and under the supervision of a qualified dental nurse, the post holder will be expected to assume a range of clinical and patient-facing responsibilities and become an effective member of our dental team.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;The post holder’s responsibilities will include:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Following initial training and under the supervision of a qualified dental nurse, the post holder will be expected to:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Promote and maintain health and safety in the workplace&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Implement and perform satisfactory infection control in the dental environment&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Provide chairside support for the patient and operator during the assessment of oral health, treatment planning and the prevention and treatment of oral and dental diseases and disorders&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Communicate effectively with patients, their families and with other health professionals involved in their care&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Deal with medical emergencies as a member of the dental team&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Actively engage with Smile Together teams and participate in audit activities, planning and development sessions, and in-house meetings etc&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Be responsible for safe working and practice on a day-to-day basis in sites of clinical activity, ensuring compliance with clinical governance and legislation, appropriate health, safety and security procedures within the work area, and report accidents, incidents and near misses using the Smile Together incident reporting procedure&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Participate in appropriate community dental and oral health promotion activities – for examples see more about our Smiles at Sea initiative at smiletogether.co.uk/smilesatsea/ and our oral health campaign at brightersmiles.org.uk&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Undertake other reasonable duties as requested by the Clinical Lead dental Nurse, Clinical Operations Manager and Smile Together Management Team&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
